short verison at the bottom i feel that this is among the greats here on steam it has one of the most active and varied communities of any game ive ever played and for the most part a good community at that if you dont like voice chat id recommend against playing on rp servers the game is great if you have no idea what to do due to its vast array of content both official and community made its also very easy to get into with clear labeling of all the tools you have at your disposal although it can get very complex and time consuming if you let it overall a amazing game for pretty much any type of gamer due to its shear amount of content which is unmatched in my opinion by any other game on steam furthermore its not incredibly expensive for the base game but buyer beware you will need all the source games in order to have the full experience although its very easy to have fun with none of them or very few such as cs source and tf2 these are all you really need if you want to play online to the full experience i personally would recommend this game to everyone i know that has any interest in a physics based sandbox with combat elements or just to mess around for the price its a great game to look into and it goes on sale often so even if you dont pick it up at full price consider getting it during a sale short review pros good physics engine near unlimited content workshop easy to get into great multiplayer lots of modes good price for the amount of content single player is just as good ability to have complete freedom over what you do great sandbox gameplay cons may have to buy additional games to have to complete experience mic spam poor combat model graphics are dated in some places resource intensive may need a good computer may need to download packs for servers manually greifing is common in some multiplayer game types little help from ingame tutorials lots of tutorials online
