garrys mod is a modification for the 2004 game halflife 2 it adds features which enable the player to have a sandbox experience sandbox being building stuff like houses or robots there is also a multiplayer mode where people can show off creations or battle it out with halflife 2 weapons then there is also content that can be used from other games css is almost required for a good gmod experience the community then expand the game to add more gamemodes and other addons like new weapons or nonplayable characters graphics cant really be judged its graphics are basically of 2004 standard and since hl2 had good graphics for its time gmod gets good graphics too if it was made in 2004 graphics  98  10 there is no story music artwork or any of that you cant say anything about this game now for my experience i wasted 400 hours that id never get back 10% of it went to sandbox trying to make animations and screwing around with npcs and console commands 5% went to gamemodes like prop hunt or trouble in terrorist town 1% of it went to playtesting my wip gamemode now the last 84% i spent on darkrp i dont like darkrp butbut but but but i cant stop ill tell you why going gun dealer just to purchase guns so i can raid the pd as hobo hearing the cries of children as i rdm them arresting admins while being in a sit its all too fun stealing cars then using them in street races street racing as a taxi driver kidnapping a police officer killing that police officer scamming people in exchange for death prop climbing into bases destroying their money printers its all too fun also you can have fun with the other 16% i spent its probably more worth your time overall garrys mod gets a 95  10 it is fun and wastes all your time it has a wide variety of gamemodes and new content always coming out it doesnt get a full 10 because the amount of annoying children on this game is over 9000
